messages.content: ComfyUI-MuseV is a custom node or plugin for ComfyUI that utilizes a stable diffusion model to generate images and videos.
What is the main functionality of ComfyUI-MuseV?
The main functionality of ComfyUI-MuseV is to generate images and videos using a stable diffusion model.
To use ComfyUI-MuseV, you'll need to have ComfyUI installed and then add the ComfyUI-MuseV custom node or plugin to the interface.
Is there a license associated with ComfyUI-MuseV?
Yes, ComfyUI-MuseV is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
Can I distribute ComfyUI-MuseV under different licensing terms?
No, ComfyUI-MuseV is only licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0. It cannot be distributed under different licensing terms.
What are the limitations of ComfyUI-MuseV?
ComfyUI-MuseV is provided 'as is', without warranties or conditions of any kind, either express or implied. It is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
What can I do if I encounter issues with ComfyUI-MuseV?
For any issues with ComfyUI-MuseV, you can refer to the documentation, reach out to the community for support, or contact the developers directly.
What is the origin of the KDPM2DiscreteScheduler with ancestral sampling in ComfyUI-MuseV, and who created the scheduler?

The KDPM2DiscreteScheduler with ancestral sampling in ComfyUI-MuseV is inspired by the paper 'Elucidating the Design Space of Diffusion-Based Generative Models,' and the scheduler is ported from and created by Katherine Crowson, with the original codebase sourced from Katherine's repository at [crowsonkb/k-diffusion](https://github.com/crowsonkb/k-diffusion).
